.TH "snd_hda_set_vmaster_tlv" 9 "snd_hda_set_vmaster_tlv" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hda_set_vmaster_tlv \- Set TLV for a virtual master control
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" snd_hda_set_vmaster_tlv
.BI "(struct hda_codec *codec "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t nid "  ","
.BI "int dir "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *tlv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
HD-audio codec
.IP "nid" 12
NID of a reference widget
.IP "dir" 12
#HDA_INPUT or #HDA_OUTPUT
.IP "tlv" 12
TLV data to be stored, at least 4 elements
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set (static) TLV data for a virtual master volume using the AMP caps
obtained from the reference NID.
The volume range is recalculated as if the max volume is 0dB.
